East 35th Street, south of Ave. R, near the west side of the Stroom Kill Trail, showing the Johannes Lott house, which was destroyed between 1905 and 1910.

About 1910.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(1)
Ave. R, at about East 35th Street, showing a view of the beams of the razed Johannes Lott barn. This property, upon which stood the house and barns, was purchased from Coert Voorhies in 1719 for $(?)11,000. A section of the house was completed in 1775. This house was subsequently moved to about 1940 East 36th Street, by Hendrick I. Lott, in the middle of the 19th century. He added the extensions to the house. After many years of unoccupancy it was demolished after Set. 1905.

May 12, 1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing more of the old barn beams.

1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same as No. 2.

1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4)
A more extensive view, and showing some of the surrounding area. Note on the left, the remains of the house foundation.

1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
